  - Address actionable clang-tidy warnings across source files
  - Fix license badge link

Version 1.7.0

Feb-2026, Performance improvements
  - Switch Data storage from row-major to column-major for cache locality
  - Write whole sensor columns per putVars call instead of splitting at NaN gaps
  - Use unordered containers for O(1) sensor name lookups
Feb-2026, New features
  - Add --batch-size option to cap HDF5 metadata memory usage (default 100)
  - Add --compression/-z option to control zlib compression level (default 5)
  - Add INSTALL.sh quick-start build+test+install script
  - Merge mkTwo.py directory-walking into mkOne.py
Feb-2026, Bug fixes
  - Fix --skipFirst off-by-one in NetCDF record writing
  - Fix --skipMission/--keepMission consuming positional arguments
  - Fix NC_ERANGE writing inf to NC_FLOAT variables
  - Fix Data::load() not pruning mData when sensor.read() throws
  - Fix swapped output filename suffix in mkTwo.py (sdb.nc -> sbd.nc)
  - Add fill values for NC_BYTE (-127) and NC_SHORT (-32768) variables
Feb-2026, Build and CI
  - Prevent in-source builds and add build/ to .gitignore
  - Add cross-platform release workflow with binary packages
  - Upgrade codecov-action to v5 with upload token
  - Add concurrency group to release workflow
  - Drop macOS 13 Intel build from release workflow
  - Add monthly dependency update check workflow
  - Update spdlog from v1.15.0 to v1.17.0
  - Update Catch2 from v3.7.1 to v3.13.0
Feb-2026, Code quality
  - Fix clang-tidy warnings: assignment-in-if-condition, implicit bool
    conversions, uninitialized Sensor members, modernize destructors
  - Re-enable bugprone-assignment-in-if-condition in clang-tidy CI
  - Fix license badge link to use master branch instead of main
Feb-2026, Documentation
  - Add fuzz testing, license, C++17, and platform badges to README
  - Document performance notes and batch-size in CLAUDE.md

